19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13-120 of Title 70, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. There is hereby established a Technical Assistance Center
24 for Educational Excellence (TACEE) under the State Board of
Req. No. 11710 Page 1

1 Educ ation. The purpose of TACEE shall be to support and build
2 capacity within schools to create learning environments across the
3 state that support all students, with a particular emphasis on
4 students with disabilities.
5 B. TACEE shall:
6 1. Ensure each child with a disability has access to
7 educational services, resources, and support;
8 2. Ensure educators and administrators have access to training,
9 resources, and support;
10 3. Assist students with disabilities in developing skills for
11 postsecondary education, employment, independent living, and full
12 participation within the community; and
13 4. Develop a statewide action plan that leverages key areas of
14 strength and identifies areas in need of enhancement specific to
15 supporting students with disabilities and new teachers in the field
16 of education.
17 C. 1. Professional development for educators and
18 administrators provided by TACEE shall include ongoing training and
19 coaching to support best practices in education including skills,
20 strategies, and approaches to the planning, instruction, and
21 assessment of students of all abilities. Particular focus shall be
22 given to the instruction of students with disabilities in general
23 education settings. Professional development may be provided
24
Req. No. 11710 Page 2

1 virt ually and shall include at least ten learning sessions annually
2 free of charge for each of the following groups:
3 a. general education teachers,
4 b. special education teachers,
5 c. school and district leaders,
6 d. paraprofessionals or teacher aides, and
7 e. physical education and special area teachers, such as
8 art, music, and language teachers.
9 2. TACEE shall publicize the availability of all professional
10 development sessions and shall conduct pre- and post-assessments to
11 gauge participant impact and identify areas of improvement.
12 D. TACEE shall host two annual conferences in geographically
13 diverse regions of the state each school year. The conferences
14 shall feature presentations from experts and school leaders who are
15 exemplars of best practices in Oklahoma schools.
16 E. School and district improvement facilitation provided by
17 TACEE shall aim to improve the quality of instruction for all
18 students, particularly for students with disabilities. TACEE shall
19 advertise the availability of change facilitation and shall provide
20 these services free of charge. TACEE may identify schools in need
21 of school and district improvement facilitation using data on least
22 restrictive environment placements from the State Department of
23 Education.
