1 F. TACEE shall develop a website for the dissemination of
2 materials, strategies, informational videos, lesson plans, or other
3 relevant materials to support educators and administrators on high
4 quality instruction for students with disabilities.
5 G. TACEE shall be in direct alignment with the State Plan for
6 P.L. No. 114-95, also known as the Every Student Succeeds Act
7 (ESSA), and the State Performance Plan/Annual Performance Report
8 (SPP/APR), which strongly promotes high quality education for all
9 students and specifically students with disabilities.
10 H. TACEE shall be under the direct administration of the State
11 Board of Education but shall be staffed by an outside entity
12 selected through a Request for Proposals (RFP). The RFP shall be
13 open to entities, including nonprofit organizations, located or
14 operating within the state and Oklahoma institutions of higher
15 education. Additional qualifications may be determined by the
16 Board.
17 I. On or before December 1 of each calendar year, the Board
18 shall electronically submit a report to the Speaker of the House of
19 Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
20 Senate on TACEE, including but not limited to information on the
21 number of individuals and entities served and data on the
22 evaluations of the effectiveness of TACEE.
23 J. The Board may promulgate rules to implement the provisions
24 of this section.
